Gobirawa village in Safana local government is reportedly about to be attacked by armed bandits, Daily Trust gathered. The bandits on motorcycles, numbering over 200, according to locals, have surrounded the village, chanting war songs. A source, who confided in our reporter, said already the villagers and some vigilante members were gearing up for any eventual attack. He said supports from neighbouring villages and armed security personnel was being awaited, saying the council officials have been informed. ‎Details later. Banditry still haunts Zamfara’s ‘ghost’ villages Fears over Kaduna bandits being ‘next Boko Haram’...many villages deserted after attacks Katsina: Armed bandits kill one, injure another in village ‎